5:
For a guy who's here to pick up his
daughter, you sure have a lot of
bodyguards with you.
8:
This is my land, and you're
trespassing on it. I merely went to
the lengths I deemed appropriate to
deal with you.
11:
Echo. Is your head stuck in the
clouds again? Imagining
non-existent friends?
13:
If you do go, you'd just get hurt and
disappointed again. It's all a crude
imitation, and you know it. That's not
where you really belong.
18:
Huh? What the hell is that supposed
to mean?
22:
What was her name again?
Narcissa?
25:
Yes, that meddlesome
"environmentalist". I will admit, she
did have spirit. A powerful drive.
28:
But what did you do when she no
longer had a place to call her own?
Did you help her? No, you did
nothing.
30:
Let's go, Echo. You'll accomplish
nothing just repeating the past. It's a
waste of time.
45:
But... Isn't this really important to
you?!
49:
Yes. And that's why I want you to
have it.
53:
I... had a lot of fun with you here
today. Like one of those real
summer vacations I've heard about.
65: I hope you don't think me cruel.
68:
The more you pretend to be her
equals, the more miserable that
makes her. Understand this.
70: Don't talk to my daughter ever again.
79:
I... can't pretend to know exactly
what's going on in Echo's life... But...
83:
One thing I can be sure of: she
looked like she was in pain while
talking with her dad. Her smile
disappeared!
86:
Let's talk to her one more time. She
said she wanted to go that spot
from her memories, right?
88:
We can't let things end like this! Let's
talk to her, Primula!
93:
I also want to see her. I... want to
know how she really feels about all
this.
100:
Man. There really IS nothing to do
here. I haven't done anything but
drink all day!
103:
I don't mind. Surely that type of rest
is precisely what we need right now?
108:
Stella! Light! Nimbus! We're heading
out again!
112:
Oh? Do be careful then, it's rather
dark outside.
121:
They're off to see their friend. That's
what being young's all about, right?
123:
That being said, I do think they'd
benefit from some backup. Would
you bunch be willing to lend a hand?
127: Huh? The hell do you need us for?
131:
Isn't it clear? They need to bring out
the big guns. Luckily, I came packing.
136:
Did a preliminary check. No articles
unaccounted for.
138:
Hm. So they weren't onto us after all.
They really just got roped into
coming here by my daughter.
141:
Fine, then. Proceed with operations
as usual.
157: Y-you two! How did you get here?!
160:
Hehe. Primula's flowers did most of
the heavy lifting, really.
163:
We wanted to see you one more
time. We weren't satisfied with how
things left off last time...
166:
We heard what your father had to
say, but...
169:
We still want to go with you! To that
precious place from your memories!
174:
Either that, or throw them all away
and move forward... 
By my side.
176:
I thought so.
You and I...
184:
It'll be okay! We've got the others on
our side too, after all! We can do this
together
188:
I'm so sorry, but... I can't! I can't do
this.
195:
I feel terrible, especially after you
went through so much trouble doing
all this for me, but...
199:
I'm not strong like you! I don't have
what it takes.
202:
Echo? There's no need to go all
apologetic like this! You haven't
done anything!
206:
It's not just my father. She said the
same thing about me too.
210:
That I'm not like others.
That I'm... different.
